You really _shouldn&#39;t_ be using System libraries to control user input, _especially_ in Unity. Use the ``Cursor.lockState`` and ``Cursor.visible`` properties to control the cursor. In particular, it seems like what you want to do is lcok the cursor to the centre of the screen. This can be done with the following:

```csharp
/**
 * Locks the cursor to the centre of the game window.
 */
private void LockCursor()
{
    Cursor.lockState = CursorLockMode.Locked;
}

// ...
// In some MonoBehaviour...
private void Start()
{
    LockCursor();
}
```

Refer to the [documentation](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Cursor-lockState.html) for more info.

